   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PPI-South Africa City-Wide Tournament</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PeacePlayers International will unite more than 1,000 students from 7 different areas of KwaZulu-Natal, South Africa for an all-day City-Wide Tournament.  Each team is composed of a combination of children from each of the 7 different urban, township, and rural areas. The tournament creates a rare atmosphere where kids from various backgrounds get a chance to play together in a safe environment. Our belief is that, &quot;children who learn to play together, can learn to live together.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
